1) Create a github account

2) Verify your account by checking your email

3) Create a repo on github or find one you want. 
- If you want someone else's repo, they have to go to their repo settings on github.com and add you as a collaborator, and then you will get an email and accept

4) Clone the repo using 'git clone <http url>' in the terminal

5) Set your login info using 'git config --global user.email <your-email>' and 'git config --global user.name <your-name>' and windows will pop up with a little window for logging into your git account

6) Make some changes to the files

7) cd into the repo and run 'git add <files>' and 'git commit -m "message"' and 'git push'